sql:
SELECT method_name
FROM testing_methods
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) as active_test_methods_count
FROM testing_methods
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT AVG(duration) AS average_duration
FROM test_runs
WHERE test_environment = 'Staging';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS failed_run_count
FROM test_runs
WHERE result = 'Fail';

SELECT COUNT(issue_id) AS resolved_issues
FROM issues
WHERE status = 'Resolved';

SELECT plan_id, test_environment
FROM test_plans
WHERE project_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_test_plans
FROM test_plans
WHERE is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "sailing in the stormy seas of complexity" refers to methods with higher cyclomatic complexity;
- "still afloat" translates to active methods (is_active = 1);
- "equipped with the most modern navigation charts" refers to the latest metrics (is_latest = 1);
- The query orders results in descending order of average complexity, highlighting those with the highest complexity first.
